  "texts": [
    "This constraint necessitates traversing each element of the table, consequently leading to a substantial number of negative samplings.",
    "This explicit way of assigning a fixed label to each element can not cope with scenarios when one element requires multiple labels, leading to the inability to recognize all triples and confusion in the regions where triple labels intersect.",
    "Additionally, certain decoding strategies, designed in response to this approach, often result in incorrectly matched labels for a triple.",
    "To address the aforementioned issues at a fundamental level, instead of explicitly labeling all the elements, we formulate a fresh perspective to implicitly fill the tables using a block-covered approach.",
    "In this method, blocks defined by four edges (up, down, right, left) and one level are refined within a three-dimensional table (multiple two-dimensional tables stacked together)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In this method, blocks defined by four edges (up, down, right, left) and one level are refined within a three-dimensional table (multiple two-dimensional tables stacked together)."
